Salient Trust Company Lta Cut By $442,800 Its Halliburton Co (HAL) Holding, Customers Bancorp Has 1.79 Sentiment


					
						July 24, 2017 - By Darrin Black

Salient Trust Company Lta decreased Halliburton Co (HAL) stake by 58.16% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Salient Trust Company Lta sold 8,200 shares as Halliburton Co (HAL)’s stock declined 11.04%. The Salient Trust Company Lta holds 5,900 shares with $319,000 value, down from 14,100 last quarter. Halliburton Co now has $36.31B valuation. The stock declined 3.61% or $1.6 reaching $42.78 per share. About 8.60M shares traded. Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL) has risen 19.03% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has outperformed by 2.33% the S&P500.







Customers Bancorp, Inc. is a bank holding firm engaged in banking activities through its subsidiary, Customers Bank (the Bank). The company has market cap of $851.69 million. The Bank provides financial services and products to small and middle market businesses, not-for-profits, and clients through its branches and offices in Southeastern Pennsylvania (Bucks, Berks, Chester, Delaware and Philadelphia Counties), Rye Brook, Melville and New York, New York (Westchester, Suffolk and New York Counties), Hamilton, New Jersey (Mercer County), Providence, Rhode Island (Providence County), Portsmouth, New Hampshire (Rockingham County) and Boston, Massachusetts (Suffolk County). It has a 10.48 P/E ratio. The Bank also provides liquidity to the mortgage market nationwide through the operation of its loans to mortgage banking companies.
Tieton Capital Management Llc holds 5.72% of its portfolio in Customers Bancorp Inc for 204,932 shares. First Wilshire Securities Management Inc owns 392,301 shares or 4.02% of their US portfolio. Moreover, Hillcrest Asset Management Llc has 2.9% invested in the company for 413,035 shares. The Wisconsin-based 1492 Capital Management Llc has invested 2.28% in the stock. Aristotle Capital Boston Llc, a Massachusetts-based fund reported 385,731 shares.
Since January 1, 0001, it had 0 buys, and 5 selling transactions for $15.95 million activity. 
 About 31,150 shares traded. Customers Bancorp Inc (CUBI) has risen 10.83% since July 24, 2016 and is uptrending. It has underperformed by 5.87% the S&P500.
Ratings analysis reveals 100% of Customers Bancorp’s analysts are positive. Out of 2 Wall Street analysts rating Customers Bancorp, 2 give it “Buy”, 0 “Sell” rating, while 0 recommend “Hold”. The lowest target is $40.0 while the high is $40.0. The stock’s average target of $40 is 43.22% above today’s ($27.93) share price. CUBI was included in 2 notes of analysts from December 8, 2016. The stock has “Outperform” rating by FBR Capital on Thursday, December 8. Maxim Group maintained the shares of CUBI in report on Monday, December 19 with “Buy” rating.
Investors sentiment increased to 1.12 in 2016 Q4. Its up 0.24, from 0.88 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 64 investors sold HAL shares while 301 reduced holdings. 125 funds opened positions while 283 raised stakes. 680.96 million shares or 2.31% more from 665.59 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Fifth Third Natl Bank holds 0% or 12,285 shares in its portfolio. Manitoba – Canada-based Tetrem Cap Mngmt Ltd has invested 1.3% in Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL). Lombard Odier Asset (Usa) has invested 1.35% in Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL). Price T Rowe Assocs Md has 0.03% invested in Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL) for 2.46 million shares. Blackrock accumulated 1.81M shares or 0.14% of the stock. Webster Financial Bank N A holds 0.03% or 3,250 shares in its portfolio. Great West Life Assurance Can reported 0.15% in Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL). Blb&B Advisors Limited Liability Corp, a Pennsylvania-based fund reported 6,630 shares. Strategic Serv Incorporated has 0.07% invested in Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL). Brinker Incorporated accumulated 0.31% or 101,376 shares. Nordea Mgmt Ab reported 919,426 shares. Parkside Bancorp And Tru reported 467 shares or 0.01% of all its holdings. Central Financial Bank stated it has 1,500 shares or 0.02% of all its holdings. Commercial Bank Of Nova Scotia stated it has 0.01% of its portfolio in Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL). Reinhart owns 7,950 shares or 0.04% of their US portfolio.
Among 36 analysts covering Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL), 32 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 4 Hold. Therefore 89% are positive. Halliburton Company had 112 analyst reports since July 21, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. The stock has “Outperform” rating by FBR Capital on Friday, October 14. Cowen & Co maintained the stock with “Market Perform” rating in Thursday, October 20 report. Deutsche Bank maintained the stock with “Buy” rating in Thursday, July 21 report. The firm earned “Hold” rating on Tuesday, February 16 by Argus Research. The company was maintained on Friday, July 7 by Cowen & Co. The firm earned “Buy” rating on Thursday, September 3 by HSBC. The firm has “Buy” rating given on Thursday, July 20 by Seaport Global. The firm earned “Neutral” rating on Wednesday, June 21 by Seaport Global. The company was upgraded on Monday, October 3 by Societe Generale. The firm has “Buy” rating by Zacks given on Tuesday, August 11.
Since January 26, 2017, it had 2 insider purchases, and 5 insider sales for $4.40 million activity. $196,613 worth of stock was sold by Jones Myrtle L on Friday, January 27. 89,300 Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL) shares with value of $4.76M were sold by MCCOLLUM MARK A. 5,390 shares were bought by GERBER MURRY, worth $307,817. $36,453 worth of Halliburton Company (NYSE:HAL) shares were sold by Miller Jeffrey Allen. The insider Albrecht William E bought 8,000 shares worth $370,608.
Salient Trust Company Lta increased Pepsico Inc (NYSE:PEP) stake by 16,560 shares to 152,853 valued at $15.99 million in 2016Q4. It also upped General Mls Inc (NYSE:GIS) stake by 22,915 shares and now owns 161,071 shares. Weingarten Rlty Invs (NYSE:WRI) was raised too. 








